article.headline: Commodores' Earley, Ramsey combine for 41 points
article.linkText: Vandy uses 15-0 first-half run to beat Siena
article.story:
NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Ashley Earley scored 21 points to lead Vanderbilt (No. 15 ESPN/USA Today, No. 14 AP) over Siena 76-47 in the championship game of the Vanderbilt Tournament on Saturday.

Vanderbilt (4-0) forced 12 turnovers in a 15-0 first-half run. Abi Ramsey added 20 points and earned MVP honors. Her 3-pointer extended the Commodores' lead to 38-11 just before halftime.

Dee Davis had 14 points and Carla Thomas 13 for Vanderbilt.

Reserve Melissa Manzer scored a team-high 11 points for Siena (1-3).

With the win, Vanderbilt extended its string of home-court nonconference victories to 46.
